com.hcl.domino.richtext.records

Enum RecordType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<RecordType>
      • com.hcl.domino.richtext.records.RecordType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<RecordType>

    public enum RecordType
extends Enum<RecordType>
    Enum with all available CD record types, which are the building blocks of Notes rich text.

      Actions may be presented to the user as buttons on the action button bar or as options on the "Actions" menu.

      ACTIONBAR
      The designer of a form or view may define custom actions for that form or view.
      The attributes for the button bar are stored in the CDACTIONBAR record in the $ACTIONS and/or $V5ACTIONS item for the design note describing the form or view.
      ACTIONBAREXT
      This CD record defines the Action Bar attributes.
      ACTIONEXT
      New field attributes have been added in Notes/Domino 6.
      To preserve compatibility with existing applications, the new attributes have been placed in this extension to the CDACTION record.
      ALTERNATEBEGIN
      Documents converted from HTML (Hyper-Text Markup Language), usually from a World Wide Web source, may contain "active object" instructions (such as a Java applet).
      An active object may have an alternate representation which is to be displayed if the active object is not supported or is disabled.
      ALTERNATEEND
      This record marks the end of a sequence of CD records comprising the alternate representation of an active object.
      For more information, please see the entry for CDALTERNATEBEGIN.
      ALTTEXT
      Documents stored on a Lotus Domino server that are viewed via a Web browser may contain elements that cannot be displayed by the browser.
      These elements may have alternate text that the browser will display in their place.
      The alternate text is stored in a CDALTTEXT record.
      ANCHOR
      An anchor hotlink points to a specific location in a rich text field of a document.
      That target location is identified by a CDANCHOR record containing a specified text string.
      When the anchor hotlink is selected by a user, Notes displays the anchor location in the target document.
      AREAELEMENT
      An AREA element defines the shape and coordinates of a region within a client side image MAP.
      BACKGROUNDCOLOR 
      BACKGROUNDPROPERTIES
      This CD Record gives information pertaining to Background Properties for a box.

      This structure defines the appearance of the bar used with collapsible sections.

      Not all CD records are enclosed within a CDBEGINRECORD/CDENDRECORD combination.

      BIDI_TEXTEFFECT

      The bitmap data is divided into segments to optimize data storage within Domino.
      It is recommended that each segment be no larger than 10k bytes.
      BLOBPART
      This CD record is used in conjunction with CD record CDEVENT.
      If a CDEVENT record has an ActionType of ACTION_TYPE_JAVASCRIPT then CDBLOBPART contains the JavaScript code.
      BORDERINFO

      A color table is one of the optional records following a CDBITMAPHEADER record.

      EMBEDDEDEDITCTL

      This CD Record defines the attributes of an embedded outline.

      EMBEDDEDSCHEDCTL

      EMBEDDEDVIEW
      This CD Record describes a view as an embedded element.
      A CDEMBEDDEDVIEW record will be preceded by a CDPLACEHOLDER record.
      Further description of the embedded view can be found in the CD record CDPLACEHOLDER.
      EMBEDEXTRA_INFO

      FRAME

      FRAMESET

      GRAPHIC
      The CDGRAPHIC record contains information used to control display of graphic objects in a document.
      This record marks the beginning of a composite graphic object, and must be present for any graphic object to be loaded or displayed.
      HEADER
      Contains the header or footer used in a document.
      HORIZONTALRULE
      Specifies a horizontal line.
      HOTSPOTBEGIN
      This structure specifies the start of a "hot" region in a rich text field.
      Clicking on a hot region causes some other action to occur.
      For instance, clicking on a popup will cause a block of text associated with that popup to be displayed.
      HOTSPOTEND
      This structure specifies the end of a hot region in a rich text field.
      HREF 
      HREF2 
      HREFBORDER 
      HTML_ALTTEXT 
      HTMLBEGIN
      Text in a rich-text field can have the "Pass-Thru HTML" attribute.
      Pass-through HTML text is not translated to the Domino rich text format.
      Pass-through HTML text is marked by CDHTMLBEGIN and CDHTMLEND records.
      HTMLEND
      Text in a rich-text field can have the "Pass-Thru HTML" attribute.
      Pass-through HTML text is not translated to the Domino rich text format.
      Pass-through HTML text is marked by CDHTMLBEGIN and CDHTMLEND records.
      HTMLFORMULA
      A CDHTMLFORMULA record contains a formula used to generate either an attribute or alternate HTML text for a Java applet.
      HTMLHEADER
      This record is included for future use.
      Applications should not generate these records.
      Domino and Notes will ignore this record.
      HTMLNAME 
      HTMLSEGMENT
      This record is included for future use.
      IDNAME
      This CD record describes the HTML field properties, ID, Class, Style, Title, Other and Name associated for any given field defined within a Domino Form
      IGNORE
      Used to ignore a block of CD records for a particular version of Notes
      IMAGEHEADER
      This structure is used to define a JPEG or GIF Image that is part of a Domino document.
      The CDIMAGEHEADER structure follows a CDGRAPHIC structure.
      CDIMAGESEGMENT structure(s) then follow the CDIMAGEHEADER.
      IMAGEHEADER2 
      IMAGESEGMENT
      This structure defines the image segment data of a JPEG or GIF image and follows a CDIMAGEHEADER structure.
      The number of segments in the image is contained in the CDIMAGEHEADER and specifies the number of CDIMAGESEGMENT structures to follow.
      INLINE
      This CD Record gives information pertaining to shared resources and/or shared code in a form.
      A CDINLINE record may be preceded by a CDBEGINRECORD and followed by a CDRESOURCE and then a CDENDRECORD.
      KEYWORD
      This structure is the header of a record containing the predefined keywords allowed for a field (defined by a CDFIELD record).
      LARGE_PARAGRAPH 
      LAYER
      The definition for a layer on a form is stored as CD records in the $Body item of the form note.
      A layer is comprised of a Layer Object Run (pointer to box that represents the layer), Box Run and Position Data.
      LAYOUT
      The definition for a layout region on a form is stored as CD records in the $Body item of the form note.
      The layout region begins with a CDLAYOUT record and ends with a CDLAYOUTEND record.
      Other records in the layout region define buttons, graphics, fields, or other rich text elements.
      LAYOUTBUTTON
      A button in a layout region of a form is defined by a CDLAYOUTBUTTON record.
      This record must be between a CDLAYOUT record and a CDLAYOUTEND record.
      This record is usually followed by other CD records identifying text, graphical, or action elements associated with the button.
      LAYOUTEND
      The CDLAYOUTEND record marks the end of the elements defining a layout region within a form.
      LAYOUTFIELD
      A field in a layout region of a form is defined by a CDLAYOUTFIELD record.
      This record must be between a CDLAYOUT record and a CDLAYOUTEND record.
      This record is usually followed by other CD records identifying text, graphical, or action elements associated with the field.
      LAYOUTGRAPHIC
      A graphical element in a layout region of a form is defined by a CDLAYOUTGRAPHIC record.
      This record must be between a CDLAYOUT record and a CDLAYOUTEND record.
      This record is usually followed by other CD records identifying text, graphical, or action elements associated with the graphical element.
      LAYOUTTEXT
      A text element in a layout region of a form is defined by a CDLAYOUTTEXT record.
      This record must be between a CDLAYOUT record and a CDLAYOUTEND record.
      This record is usually followed by other CD records identifying text, graphical, or action elements associated with the element
      LINK 
      LINK2
      This structure implements a document link in a rich text field.
      It contains an index into a Doc Link Reference List.
      A Doc Link Reference (a NOTELINK structure) contains all the information necessary to open the specified document from any database on any server.
      LINKCOLORS
      Color properties to various HTML Links.
      LINKEXPORT 
      LINKEXPORT2
      This structure is used to create a document link in a rich text field.
      It contains all the information necessary to open the specified document from any database on any server.
      LSOBJECT
      The CD record contains Lotus Script object code.
      MACMETAHEADER
      Identifies a Macintosh metafile embedded in a rich text field.
      This record must be preceded by a CDGRAPHIC record.
      Since metafiles can be large, but Domino and Notes has an internal limit of 65,536 bytes (64kB) for a segment, a metafile may be divided into segments of up to 64kB;
      each segment must be preceded by a CDMACMETASEG record.
      MACMETASEG
      A portion of a Macintosh metafile.
      MAPELEMENT
      Part of a client side image MAP which describes each region in an image and indicates the location of the document to be retrieved when the defined area is activated..
      MAPIBINARY 
      METAFILE 
      NATIVEIMAGE 
      NESTEDTABLEBEGIN 
      NESTEDTABLECELL 
      NESTEDTABLEEND

      OLEOBJPH 
      OLERTMARKER
      This record is simply a marker in an OLE rich text hot spot that indicates that an OLE object with an associated rich text field (a $OLEObjRichTextField item) was updated by Release 4.6 or later of Domino or Notes.
      PABDEFINITION
      This structure specifies a format for paragraphs in a rich-text field.
      PABFORMREF 
      PABHIDE
      This record contains the "Hide When" formula for a paragraph attributes block.
      PABREFERENCE
      This structure is placed at the start of each paragraph in a rich-text field, and specifies which CDPABDEFINITION is used as the format for the paragraph.
      PARAGRAPH
      This structure defines the start of a new paragraph within a rich-text field.
      Each paragraph in a rich text field may have different style attributes, such as indentation and interline spacing.
      PATTERNTABLE
      A pattern table is one of the optional records following a CDBITMAPHEADER record.
      The pattern table is used to compress repetitive bitmap data.
      PDEF_ACTION 
      PDEF_MAIN

      PLACEHOLDER
      A CDPLACEHOLDER record stores additional information about various embedded type CD records, such as CDEMBEDDEDCTL, CDEMBEDDEDOUTLINE and other embedded CD record types defined in HOTSPOTREC_TYPE_xxx.
      PMMETAHEADER
      Identifies a Presentation Manger GPI metafile embedded in a rich text field.
      This record must be preceded by a CDGRAPHIC record.
      PMMETASEG
      A portion of a Presentation Manager GPI metafile.
      POSITIONING
      This CD record contains position information for a layer box.
      PRETABLEBEGIN
      This CD record provides additional table properties, expanding the information provided in CDTABLEBEGIN.
      It will only be recognized in Domino versions 5.0 and greater.
      REGIONBEGIN

      STYLENAME
      This structure stores the style name for a Paragraph Attributes Block (PAB).
      TABLEBEGIN
      This structure specifies the beginning of a table.
      It contains information about the format and size of the table.
      Use this structure when accessing a table in a rich text field.
      As of R5, this structure is preceded by a CDPRETABLEBEGIN structure.
      The CDPRETABLEBEGIN structure specifies additional table properties.
      TABLECELL
      This structure specifies the cell of a table.
      TABLECELL_COLOR 
      TABLECELL_DATAFLAGS

      TABLECELL_HREF

      TABLEEND
      This structure specifies the end of a table.
      TABLELABEL

      TABLEROWHEIGHT

      TARGET

      TEXTPROPERTIESTABLE

      TEXTPROPERTY
      This CD record contains language information for a field or a run of rich text.
      TIFF 
      TIMERINFO

      WINMETAHEADER
      Identifies a Windows Graphics Device Interface (GDI) metafile embedded in a rich text field.
      This record must be preceded by a CDGRAPHIC record.
      Since Windows GDI metafiles can be large, but Domino and Notes have an internal limit of 65,536 bytes (64kB) for a segment, a metafile may be divided into segments of up to 64kB;
      each segment must be preceded by a CDWINMETASEG record.

        public static final RecordType BITMAPHEADER
        A rich text field may contain a bitmap image. There are three types, monochrome, 8-bit mapped color, and 16-bit color; a gray scale bitmap is stored as an 8-bit color bitmap with a color table having entries [0, 0, 0], [1, 1, 1], . . . , [255, 255, 255]. All bitmaps are stored as a single plane (some graphics devices support multiple planes).

      • BITMAPSEGMENT

        public static final RecordType BITMAPSEGMENT
        The bitmap data is divided into segments to optimize data storage within Domino.
        It is recommended that each segment be no larger than 10k bytes. For best display speed, the segments sould be as large as possible, up to the practical 10k limit. A scanline must be contained within a single segment, and cannot be divided between two segments. A bitmap must contain at least one segment, but may have many segments.

      • COLORTABLE

        public static final RecordType COLORTABLE
        A color table is one of the optional records following a CDBITMAPHEADER record.
        The color table specifies the mapping between 8-bit bitmap samples and 24-bit Red/Green/Blue colors.

      • GRAPHIC

        public static final RecordType GRAPHIC
        The CDGRAPHIC record contains information used to control display of graphic objects in a document.
        This record marks the beginning of a composite graphic object, and must be present for any graphic object to be loaded or displayed.

      • PMMETASEG

        public static final RecordType PMMETASEG
        A portion of a Presentation Manager GPI metafile. This record must be preceded by a CDPMMETAHEADER record.
        Since metafiles can be large, but Domino and Notes have an internal limit of 65,536 bytes (64kB) for a segment, a metafile may be divided into segments of up to 64kB;
        each segment must be preceded by a CDPMMETASEG record.

      • WINMETASEG

        public static final RecordType WINMETASEG
        A portion of a Windows GDI metafile. This record must be preceded by a CDWINMETAHEADER record.
        Since Windows GDI metafiles can be large, but Domino and Notes have an internal limit of 65,536 bytes (64kB) for a segment, a metafile may be divided into segments of up to 64kB; each segment must be preceded by a CDWINMETASEG record.

      • TRANSPARENTTABLE

        public static final RecordType TRANSPARENTTABLE
        Bitmap Transparency Table (optionally one per bitmap). The colors in this table specify the bitmap colors that are "transparent".
        The pixels in the bitmap whose colors are in this table will not affect the background; the background will "bleed through" into the bitmap.
        The entries in the transparency table should be in the same format as entries in the color table.
        If a transparency table is used for a bitmap, it must immediately follow the CDBITMAPHEADER.

        public static final RecordType ALTERNATEBEGIN
        Documents converted from HTML (Hyper-Text Markup Language), usually from a World Wide Web source, may contain "active object" instructions (such as a Java applet).
        An active object may have an alternate representation which is to be displayed if the active object is not supported or is disabled.
